</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1525,2036]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,152,252]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName authority="(Strack, 1993)" baseAuthorityName="Strack" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[197,626,1786,1812]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hylkiae">
<emphasis box="[197,437,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Parachiton hylkiae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Strack, H. L." box="[455,617,1786,1812]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref23788" refString="Strack, H. L. (1993) The Polyplacophora of the Red Sea. Journal of the Malacological Society of Australia, 14, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1993">Strack, 1993</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is different from the other Indian Ocean species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1909" box="[1287,1427,1787,1812]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1287,1427,1787,1812]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Parachiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kaas &amp; Van Belle, 1985)" baseAuthorityName="Kaas &amp; Van Belle" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[151,712,1824,1850]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="eugenei">
<emphasis box="[151,388,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Parachiton eugenei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[405,703,1824,1850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref22049" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora). Volume 2. Suborder Ischnochitonina, Ischnochitonidae: Schizoplacinae, Callochitoninae &amp; Lepidochitoninae. E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden, 198 pp." type="book" year="1985">Kaas &amp; Van Belle, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[788,933,1824,1850]" name="Madagascar" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kaas &amp; Van Belle, 1985)" baseAuthorityName="Kaas &amp; Van Belle" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[994,1436,1824,1850]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ronaldi">
<emphasis box="[994,1111,1824,1849]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. ronaldi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[1129,1427,1824,1850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref22049" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora). Volume 2. Suborder Ischnochitonina, Ischnochitonidae: Schizoplacinae, Callochitoninae &amp; Lepidochitoninae. E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden, 198 pp." type="book" year="1985">Kaas &amp; Van Belle, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Andaman Islands have the granules of the head valve, lateral areas and postmucronal area arranged in quincunx. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kaas &amp; Van Belle, 1990)" baseAuthorityName="Kaas &amp; Van Belle" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[310,779,1898,1924]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="indecorus">
<emphasis box="[310,458,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. indecorus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[475,771,1898,1924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" refId="ref22144" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1990) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora). Volume 4. Suborder Ischnochitonina: Ischnochitonidae: Ischnochitoninae (continued). Additions to Volumes 1, 2 and 3. E. J. Brill, Leiden - New York - Kobenhavn - Koln, 402 pp." type="book" year="1990">Kaas &amp; Van Belle, 1990</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Natal, 
<collectingCountry box="[935,1089,1898,1924]" name="South Africa" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">South Africa</collectingCountry>
has the granules of the head valve closely radially grooved and lateral and postmucronal areas arranged in quincunx. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Anseeuw &amp; Terryn, 2004)" baseAuthorityName="Anseeuw &amp; Terryn" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jordanensis">
<emphasis box="[1261,1436,1936,1961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. jordanensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y." box="[159,460,1973,1999]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref20618" refString="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y. (2004) Intertidal chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the coast of Jordan, Red Sea, with the description of a new species of Parachiton Thiele, 1909. Bollettino Malacologico, suppl. 5 (2003), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">Anseeuw &amp; Terryn, 2004</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the northern Red Sea differs in the number of radiating granular rows, fewer than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Strack" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[240,357,2011,2036]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hylkiae">
<emphasis box="[240,357,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">P. hylkiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see table 
<quantity box="[482,527,2010,2036]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y." box="[535,839,2010,2036]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref20618" refString="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y. (2004) Intertidal chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the coast of Jordan, Red Sea, with the description of a new species of Parachiton Thiele, 1909. Bollettino Malacologico, suppl. 5 (2003), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">Anseeuw &amp; Terryn, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), which almost always coalesce creating a chained appearance in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Strack" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[332,453,152,177]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hylkiae">
<emphasis box="[332,453,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. hylkiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Anseeuw &amp; Terryn" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[614,790,152,177]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jordanensis">
<emphasis box="[614,790,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">P. jordanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this feature is rarely seen. The main distinguishing characters of these species are reported in 
<bibRefCitation author="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y." box="[649,954,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref20618" refString="Anseeuw, B. &amp; Terryn, Y. (2004) Intertidal chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) from the coast of Jordan, Red Sea, with the description of a new species of Parachiton Thiele, 1909. Bollettino Malacologico, suppl. 5 (2003), 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="2004">Anseeuw &amp; Terryn (2004</bibRefCitation>
: table 2). 
<taxonomicName box="[1070,1243,189,215]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Parachiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1070,1202,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Parachiton</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(Dell’Angelo 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
., 2004) has smooth lateral areas of the intermediate valves.
</paragraph>
